        "text_gNT8Jq": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Let’s be honest. — Most portable fans are completely useless. <em>They barely push any air and die after 2 hours. — </em>Neck fans tangle in your hair. Handheld fans keep one hand occupied — <em>but they don’t actually cool your core body temperature. — </em>What if there was a way to <strong>stay comfortably cool all day long</strong>, without holding anything? — Not just a gentle breeze — but <strong>turbo-charged, 18,000 RPM airflow directed right under your clothes.</strong></p>",
            "text_size": 16,
            "text_color": "#000000",
            "highlighted_text_color": "#000000",
            "highlighted_text_background": "#fcc947",
            "accent_text_color": "#006064",
            "accent_text_background": "#e0f7fa",
            "top_padding": 26,
            "bottom_padding": 0
          }
        },
        "bullet_points_BjfaLA": {
          "type": "bullet_points",
          "settings": {
            "point_1": "If you’ve ever wondered how people working 10-hour shifts in the blistering heat survive, here’s the secret: It’s not just drinking water. It’s not just sitting in the shade.",
            "icon": "arrow",
            "point_2": "It’s not just the heat — it’s the irritation that builds up slowly, making you more frustrated with every passing hour.I",
            "icon_2": "arrow",
            "point_3": "It’s not just sweating more than usual — it’s your body constantly struggling to keep up with the heat.It’s not just discomfort — it’s that overwhelming feeling of being overheated and drained at the same time.",
            "icon_3": "arrow",
            "point_4": "It’s not just doing the job — it’s doing it less efficiently.It’s not just the heat — it’s constant interruptions to your flow.It’s breaking your rhythm again and again.It’s not just time spent — it’s the drop in actual productivity.",
            "icon_4": "arrow",
